that's what I'm talking about!

165
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:55,647
直至今天, 我还在想
To this day, I wonder why the hell

166
00:06:55,649 --> 00:06:58,150
为何我会住在那里六年之久
I ever stayed down there for six long years.

167
00:06:58,152 --> 00:07:00,719
我当时也不知道可以怎办
But, see, I didn't know I could do no better.

168
00:07:00,721 --> 00:07:03,588
我以为只有白人才配有室内厕所什么的
I thought only white folks had inside toilets and things.

169
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:04,760
很多人也像这样
A lot of folks don't think

170
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:06,525
安于现状
they can do no better than they're doing now.

171
00:07:06,527 --> 00:07:07,726
那是些要改变的想法
Just something you gotta learn.

172
00:07:07,728 --> 00:07:09,661
就像很多人还去Bella的店买东西
A lot of folks still shop at Bella's.

173
00:07:09,663 --> 00:07:11,463
Bella卖的东西没问题啊, 她卖的食物也很新鲜
Ain't nothing wrong with Bella's. She got fresh food.

174
00:07:11,465 --> 00:07:13,198
我不是在说她卖的食物有没有问题
I ain't said nothing about if she got fresh food.

175
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,666
我在说她卖的价钱
I'm talking about what she charge.

176
00:07:14,668 --> 00:07:16,635
同样的货品她比A&P卖贵十美分
She charges 10 cents more than the A&P.

177
00:07:16,637 --> 00:07:18,203
A&P没为我做过什么
A&P ain't never done nothing for me.

178
00:07:18,205 --> 00:07:20,172
我会选择消费在我认为对的地方
I spend my money where I'm treated right.

179
00:07:20,244 --> 00:07:21,444
我到Bella的店里说
I go down to Bella, say,

180
00:07:21,474 --> 00:07:23,942
我要买一条面包, 星期五付钱, 她就给我了
"i need a loaf of bread, I'll pay you Friday," she gives it to me.

181
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:25,911
如果我还在
What sense that make when I got money

182
00:07:25,913 --> 00:07:27,512
其他地方消费
to spend it somewhere else

183
00:07:27,514 --> 00:07:28,947
把这个卖人情给我的人忘掉, 我还算什么?
and ignore the person who done right by me?

184
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:30,152
圣经里没教人忘恩负义
That ain't in the Bible.

185
00:07:30,154 --> 00:07:31,882
我们不是在谈论圣经
We ain't talking about what's in the Bible.

186
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:33,785
明知道她卖贵了, 还在那买东西, 这样理智吗?
What sense it make to shop there when she overcharges?

187
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:35,624
那你去你想去的地方买
Well, you do your shopping where you want to,

188
00:07:35,654 --> 00:07:37,492
我去卖过人情给我的地方买
I do my shopping where people been good to me.

189
00:07:37,522 --> 00:07:38,957
噢, 我只是不认同她卖贵了而已
Oh, I don't think it's right for her to overcharge, that's all.

190
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,492
听着, 我该走了
Look here, I got to be getting on.

191
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:41,827
Lucille都要发怒了
Lucille gonna be raising all kind of hell.

192
00:07:41,829 --> 00:07:43,595
朋友, 你要去哪, 我们还没喝完这瓶呢
Where you going, nigger? We ain't finished this pint.

193
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:44,867
先喝完吧
Come here finish this pint.

194
00:07:44,897 --> 00:07:48,767
我会留下啊, 如果你请我喝的话
Well, hell, I am, if you ever turn the bottle loose.

195
00:07:48,769 --> 00:07:50,735
我唯一要感谢A&P的地方
Only thing I'll say about the A&P is,

196
00:07:50,737 --> 00:07:53,038
就是他们让Cory在那工作
I'm glad Cory got that job down there.

197
00:07:53,538 --> 00:07:55,539
帮补一下他的开支
Help him with his school clothes and things.

198
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:57,576
Gabe搬走了, 我们有点捉襟见肘
Gabe done moved out, things getting tight around here.

199
00:07:57,578 --> 00:07:58,810
他有份工作
He got that job,

200
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,545
至少可以照顾下自己
he can start to look out for himself.

201
00:08:00,547 --> 00:08:03,782
Cory被一间大学的美式足球队录取了
Cory done got recruited by a college football team.

202
00:08:03,784 --> 00:08:06,918
我跟他说过大学的美式足球队到底是怎么一回事
I told that boy about that college football stuff.

203
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:09,821
那些白人不会让他碰美式足球的
The white man ain't gonna let him get nowhere with that football.

204
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,890
他第一次来我就跟他解释过了
I told him when he first come to me with it.

205
00:08:11,892 --> 00:08:14,693
现在你告诉我他更着迷了
Now, you come telling me he done got more tied up in it.

206
00:08:14,695 --> 00:08:16,795
他该去车行工作
He ought to get recruited in how to fix cars,

207
00:08:16,867 --> 00:08:18,467
还是做点能令他过活的事
or some way he can make a living.

208
00:08:18,497 --> 00:08:20,665
他不是想成为职业美式足球员
He ain't talking about making no living playing football.

209
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:22,701
那只是他的兴趣而已
It's just something the boys in school do.

210
00:08:22,703 --> 00:08:24,223
他们会派负责人员来
They're gonna send a recruiter by

211
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:25,774
跟你商讨, 他会跟你说
to talk to you. He'll tell you.

212
00:08:25,804 --> 00:08:26,905
他不是想成为职业美式足球员
He ain't talking about making no living playing football.

213
00:08:26,907 --> 00:08:28,640
被录取是个荣誉
It's an honor to be recruited.

214
00:08:28,642 --> 00:08:31,009
他不会走得远的, Bono就懂
It ain't gonna get him nowhere, Bono'll tell you that.

215
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:34,579
如果他跟你一样那么有运动细胞, 他会成为伟大的球员
If he be like you in sports, he gonna be all right.

216
00:08:34,581 --> 00:08:36,948
这么久以来只有两个人打棒球比你好
Ain't but two men ever played baseball good as you.

217
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:39,017
就是Babe Ruth和Josh Gibson [皆为著名棒球员]
That's Babe Ruth and Josh Gibson.

218
00:08:39,019 --> 00:08:41,553
他们就是唯一比你有更多全垒打的人
Them the only two men ever hit more home runs than you.

219
00:08:41,555 --> 00:08:43,788
打棒球给了我什么? 我没有地方上厕所
And what it ever get me? I ain't got a pot to piss in,

220
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:45,060
又或者靠此买过一间房子
or a window to throw it out of.

221
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:46,925
时代不同了, Troy
Times have changed since you were playing baseball, Troy.

222
00:08:46,927 --> 00:08:48,994
你打棒球都是战争之前了, 很多事情都改变了
That was before the war. Times have changed a lot since then.

223
00:08:48,996 --> 00:08:50,262
有什么改变了?
How the hell they done changed?

224
00:08:50,264 --> 00:08:51,863
现在很多有色人种都在球队里
They got a lot of colored boys playing ball now.

225
00:08:51,865 --> 00:08:53,298
棒球也好, 美式足球也好
Baseball and football.

226
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:56,601
Ro, 你说对了, 时代不同了, Troy
You right about that, Ro. Times have changed, Troy.

227
00:08:56,673 --> 00:08:57,973
你只是生不逢时而已
You just come along too early.

228
00:08:58,003 --> 00:09:01,706
世上没有所谓"生不逢时"
There ought not never have been no time called "too early."

229
00:09:03,009 --> 00:09:05,544
以他为例...
Now you take that fellow...

230
00:09:05,546 --> 00:09:07,078
那个以前在洋基队
What's that fellow they had playing

231
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,346
当右外野手的叫什么?
right field back then for the Yankees?

232
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:09,281
Bono, 你该记得的
You remember who I'm talking about, Bono,

233
00:09:09,311 --> 00:09:10,634
在洋基队当右外野手的那个
played right field for the Yankees.

234
00:09:10,664 --> 00:09:12,017
- Selkirk?    对, 就是他 [George Selkirk]
- Selkirk?   - Yeah, Selkirk, that's it!

235
00:09:12,019 --> 00:09:15,620
他的职业生涯打击率是.269, 你看得出了吗?
Man's batting 269, you understand? 269!

236
00:09:15,622 --> 00:09:19,291
那合理吗? 我的打击率是.432, 有37个是全垒打
What sense that make? I'm batting 432 with 37 home runs!

237
00:09:19,293 --> 00:09:22,561
他的打击率才.269, 却在洋基队里当右外野手!
He's batting 269, playing right field for the Yankees!

238
00:09:22,563 --> 00:09:24,696
我昨天看到Josh Gibson的女儿
I saw Josh Gibson's daughter yesterday.

239
00:09:24,698 --> 00:09:27,332
她穿着破烂的鞋到处跑
She's running around with raggedy shoes on her feet.

240
00:09:27,334 --> 00:09:28,934
我敢打赌Selkirk的女儿
I bet you Selkirk's daughter ain't running around

241
00:09:28,936 --> 00:09:30,869
可不是穿着什么破烂的到处走
with no raggedy shoes on her feet. I bet you that.

242
00:09:30,871 --> 00:09:32,804
现在很多职业棒球员都是有色人种了
They got a lot of colored baseball players now.

243
00:09:32,806 --> 00:09:33,942
Jackie Robinson是第一个
Jackie Robinson was the first.

244
00:09:33,944 --> 00:09:35,972
Jackie Robinson都是名星了
Folks had to wait for Jackie Robinson.

245
00:09:35,974 --> 00:09:38,877
我看过无数比Jackie Robinson还会打棒球的黑人
I done seen 100 niggers play baseball better than Jackie Robinson.

246
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:41,880
我甚至看过Jackie Robinson都进不了的球队
Hell, I seen some teams Jackie Robinson couldn't even make!

247
00:09:41,882 --> 00:09:43,114
还说什么Jackie Robinson?
What you talking about, Jackie Robinson?

248
00:09:43,116 --> 00:09:44,950
Jackie Robinson只是个无名小卒而已!
Jackie Robinson wasn't nobody!

249
00:09:44,952 --> 00:09:46,618
我要说的是如果你会打球
I'm talking about if you could play ball,

250
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,886
他们就该给你机会
then they ought to let you play.

251
00:09:47,888 --> 00:09:49,054
而不是在意你的肤色人种
Don't matter what color you are.

252
00:09:49,056 --> 00:09:50,889
还说我生不逢时
Come telling me I come along too early.

253
00:09:50,891 --> 00:09:54,092
如果你会打球, 他们就该给你机会
If you can play, then they ought to let you play.

254
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:55,727
你再继续这么喝会死的
You gonna drink yourself to death.

255
00:09:55,729 --> 00:09:57,762
不用喝那么多吧
You don't need to be drinking like that.

256
00:09:57,764 --> 00:10:00,999
噢, 死神而已, 我都见过了
Oh! Death ain't nothing. I done seen him,

257
00:10:01,001 --> 00:10:03,034
还跟他搏斗过, 不用你来跟我说
I done wrestled with him. You can't tell me nothing about death.

258
00:10:03,036 --> 00:10:06,638
死神不过是个外角的快速球
Death ain't nothing but a fastball on the outside corner,

259
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,607
而你知道我有什么能耐
and you know what I do with that.

260
00:10:08,609 --> 00:10:10,375
Bono, 看这里, 我有在说谎吗?
Look here, Bono, am I lying?

261
00:10:10,377 --> 00:10:13,345
你扔个到腰水平高度的快速球
You get one of them fastballs about waist high

262
00:10:13,347 --> 00:10:14,946
从外角扔过来
on the outside corner of the plate

263
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,815
那简直易如反掌
where you can get the meat of the bat on it,

264
00:10:16,817 --> 00:10:20,051
老天啊, 我会把它打到出场外
and, good god, you could kiss it good-bye.

265
00:10:20,053 --> 00:10:22,120
- 我在吹嘘吗?    - 不, 你在说事实
- Am I lying?   - No, you telling the truth.

266
00:10:22,192 --> 00:10:23,292
我亲眼看见过
I seen you do it.

267
00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:26,797
如果我在吹牛, 那会是天大的谎话
If I'm lying, that's 450 feet worth of lying.

268
00:10:26,827 --> 00:10:28,960
死神来我来说就是这么回事
That's all death is to me.

269
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:31,630
一个从外角扔来的快速球
A fastball on the outside corner.

270
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:33,898
我不知道你为何说起死亡了?
I don't know why you want to get on talking about death?

271
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,133
说说又没有问题
Ain't nothing wrong with talking about death.

272
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,035
那是生命的一部分啊, 每个人都必经
That's a part of life! Everybody gonna die.

273
00:10:37,037 --> 00:10:38,637
你会死, 我会死
You gonna die. I'm gonna die.

274
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:40,372
Bono会死, 天啊, 所有人都会死
Bono gonna die. Hell, we all gonna die.

275
00:10:40,374 --> 00:10:41,706
但你也没必要继续说吧
But you ain't got to talk about it.

276
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:42,841
我不喜欢说这种事
I don't like talking about it.

277
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:44,009
那是你提起的
Well, you the one brought it up.

278
00:10:44,011 --> 00:10:45,810
Bono和我刚才在说棒球
Me and Bono talking about baseball.

279
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,846
你突然说我会喝死
You come telling me I'm gonna drink myself to death.

280
00:10:47,918 --> 00:10:48,818
不是吗, Bono?
Ain't that right, Bono?

281
00:10:48,848 --> 00:10:51,416
你知道我一周只有一晚去喝酒
Now you know I drink just but one night out the week,

282
00:10:51,488 --> 00:10:52,388
那是星期五晚
that's Friday night.

283
00:10:52,418 --> 00:10:54,653
我不会喝多
I drink just enough to where I can handle it.

284
00:10:54,725 --> 00:10:55,625
然后我就会离开, 不碰它了
Then I leaves it alone. I cuts it loose.

285
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:58,123
所以你不必担心我会喝死
So, you ain't got to worry about me drinking myself to death

286
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,891
因为我不害怕死亡
'cause I ain't worrying about death.

287
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:02,727
我见过他, 跟他搏斗过
I done seen him, done wrestled with him.

288
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:03,899
跟你说, Bono
Look here, Bono.

289
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:07,132
我有天看到死神举军冲向我
I look up one day, and death is marching straight at me,

290
00:11:07,134 --> 00:11:09,401
像是阅兵时的士军队一样
like soldiers on parade.

291
00:11:09,403 --> 00:11:11,903
当时死神大军在冲向我
The army of death was marching straight at me.

292
00:11:11,905 --> 00:11:15,173
当时是1941年7月中
It was the middle of July, 1941.

293
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,742
然而却像冬天一般冷
And it got real cold, just like it be winter.

294
00:11:17,744 --> 00:11:19,177
那时候死神他啊
And it seemed like death, himself,

295
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:21,413
好像举手碰了我肩膀一下
reached out and touched me on the shoulder.

296
00:11:21,415 --> 00:11:24,883
他像我现在碰你一样, 我感受到那寒意
He touched me like I touch you now. I got cold as ice.

297
00:11:24,885 --> 00:11:26,084
死神就站在那里, 对我露出不友善的笑容
Death standing there, grinning at me.

298
00:11:26,086 --> 00:11:27,952
Troy, 别说了
Troy, why don't you hush that talk.

299
00:11:27,954 --> 00:11:31,189
我说: 死神先生, 你想要什么? 要带走我吗?
I said, "what you want, Mr. death? You be wanting me?

300
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:33,158
你不再派你的小卒来了吗?
"You done sent your army to be getting me?"

301
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:33,947
我直直的看着他
I looked him dead in the eye.

302
00:11:34,077 --> 00:11:35,164
我什么都不怕
I wasn't fearing nothing.

303
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:38,163
我准备跟他斗个你死我活, 直至现在我都是!
I was ready to tangle, just like I'm ready to tangle now!

304
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,465
圣经说要经常警惕
Bible says be ever vigilant.

305
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:42,901
所以我不会喝醉, 我还要耳听八方
So, I don't get but so drunk. I got to keep watch.

306
00:11:42,903 --> 00:11:44,703
Troy当时进了慈善医院
Troy was right down there at mercy hospital.

307
00:11:44,775 --> 00:11:45,675
你记得他那次得了肺炎
You remember he had that pneumonia,

308
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:48,006
还有发烧, 躺在床上还说些有的没的
laying there with a fever, talking plumb out his head.

309
00:11:48,008 --> 00:11:49,240
当时死神站在那盯着我
And death standing there, staring at me,

310
00:11:49,242 --> 00:11:50,909
手握着镰刀
carrying that sickle in his hand.

311
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:56,815
终于, 他说: 你想再活多一年吗?
Finally, he say, "you want to be bound over for another year?"

312
00:11:56,817 --> 00:11:58,983
他这样说
Just like that. He say,

313
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:02,921
你想再活多一年吗?
"you want to be bound over for another year?"

314
00:12:02,923 --> 00:12:06,958
我说: 去你的, 我们现在就说清楚
I said, "bound over, hell! We can settle this right now."

315
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,993
他听了后退后了点
He kinda fell back when I said that.

316
00:12:08,995 --> 00:12:10,462
我即时龙精虎猛
And all the cold went out of me.

317
00:12:10,464 --> 00:12:12,797
我伸手抢去他的镰刀
I reached down, I grabbed that sickle.

318
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,265
我用尽力气扔走它
I threw it as far as I could throw it,

319
00:12:14,267 --> 00:12:16,101
然后我们开始埋身肉搏
and me and him commenced to wrestling.

320
00:12:16,103 --> 00:12:19,838
我们打了...六...三天三夜
We wrestled for... Carry the six... Three days and three nights!

321
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,107
我不知道从哪儿来的力量
Now, I don't know where I got the strength from,

322
00:12:22,109 --> 00:12:23,975
因为他处于优势时
'cause every time he tried to get the best of me,

323
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:26,778
我重新振作
I reached way deep down inside myself,

324
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:28,113
并又得到对抗他的力量
found the strength to do him one better.

325
00:12:28,115 --> 00:12:29,914
Troy每次说起这事
Every time Troy tells that story,

326
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:31,116
都有不同的版本
he find different ways to tell it,

327
00:12:31,118 --> 00:12:32,817
不同的谎话
different things to make up.

328
00:12:32,819 --> 00:12:34,152
我没有胡说, 女人
I ain't making up nothing, woman.

