Here you go, Rose. If you don't take it,

1158
00:49:25,430 --> 00:49:27,430
接下来六个月他又要不断唠叨此事了
I'm gonna hear about it for the next six months.

1159
00:49:27,432 --> 00:49:29,265
你也可以顺道给出你的那份薪金, Troy
You can hand yours over, too, Troy.

1160
00:49:29,267 --> 00:49:31,033
Bono, 你看到他们怎对待我了吗
You see this, Bono? You see how they do me?

1161
00:49:31,035 --> 00:49:32,735
看到, Lucille也是这样做
Yeah, Lucille do me the same way.

1162
00:49:42,045 --> 00:49:44,046
嘿, 是Troy的儿子啊
Hey. Hey, there's Troy's boy!

1163
00:49:44,048 --> 00:49:45,348
Gabe叔叔, 你最近好吗?
How you doing, Uncle Gabe?

1164
00:49:45,350 --> 00:49:47,116
Lyons!
Lyons!

1165
00:49:48,753 --> 00:49:51,287
万兽之王
The king of the jungle!

1166
00:49:51,455 --> 00:49:54,457
嘿, Rose, 我有朵玫瑰花给你
Rose. Hey, Rose, I got a flower for you.

1167
00:49:54,459 --> 00:49:57,159
我亲自摘的, 就跟你名字一样的玫瑰
I picked it myself. That's the same rose like you is.

1168
00:49:57,161 --> 00:49:58,761
你真有心, Gabe
Aw, that's right nice of you, Gabe.

1169
00:49:58,763 --> 00:50:00,363
Gabe叔叔, 你最近在做什么?
What you been doing, Uncle Gabe?

1170
00:50:00,365 --> 00:50:04,100
噢, 我一直在追赶地狱之犬
Oh, I been chasing hellhounds and waiting for the time

1171
00:50:04,102 --> 00:50:06,068
并等着告诉圣彼得打开天堂的门
to tell Saint Peter to open the gates.

1172
00:50:06,070 --> 00:50:07,503
你在追赶地狱之犬?
You been chasing hellhounds, huh?

1173
00:50:07,505 --> 00:50:09,405
你做得很正确
Well, you doing the right thing, Uncle Gabe.

1174
00:50:09,407 --> 00:50:12,475
- 总有人要去赶走他们   - 是的, 我也知道
- Somebody's got to chase 'em.   - Oh, yeah, I know it.

1175
00:50:12,477 --> 00:50:15,444
魔鬼很强大, 不是那么容易打败
The devil's strong. The devil ain't no pushover.

1176
00:50:15,446 --> 00:50:18,080
地狱之犬一直在寻找人类的气息 [应为sniff, 非snip]
Hellhounds snipping at everybody's heels.

1177
00:50:18,082 --> 00:50:20,750
但我已经准备好喇叭, 等待审判日的来临
But I got my trumpet waiting on the judgment time.

1178
00:50:20,752 --> 00:50:22,451
为了哈米吉多顿之战作准备吗? [圣经中世界末日最后一战]
Waiting on the Battle of Armageddon, huh?

1179
00:50:22,453 --> 00:50:24,520
噢, 那眨眼就会结束
Oh, ain't gonna be too much of a battle

1180
00:50:24,522 --> 00:50:28,257
当上帝挥动审判之剑时
when god get to waving that judgment sword.

1181
00:50:28,259 --> 00:50:30,359
如果天堂的门关上的话, 那时候人们就得费时
But the people's gonna have a hell of a time

1182
00:50:30,361 --> 00:50:33,129
等待进入天堂了
trying to get into heaven if them gates ain't open.

1183
00:50:33,131 --> 00:50:34,497
你听到这吗, 爸?
You hear this, pop?

1184
00:50:35,198 --> 00:50:36,298
Gabe叔叔, 你人真好
Uncle Gabe, you all right.

1185
00:50:36,300 --> 00:50:37,366
Lyons.
Lyons.

1186
00:50:40,370 --> 00:50:41,570
万兽之王
The king of the jungle!

1187
00:50:42,072 --> 00:50:43,009
Gabe, 你留下来吃晚餐吗?
You stayin' for supper, Gabe?

1188
00:50:43,139 --> 00:50:44,077
你要我煮你的份吗?
You want me to fix you a plate?

1189
00:50:44,107 --> 00:50:47,209
我要份三明治就好了, 不用煮我的份
I'll just take a sandwich, Rose. I don't want no plate.

1190
00:50:47,211 --> 00:50:49,311
我喜欢用双手拿着来吃, 三明治好了
I want to eat with my hands. I'll take a sandwich.

1191
00:50:49,313 --> 00:50:51,781
你呢Lyons? 留下吗? 在煮牛小排呢
What about you, Lyons? You stayin'? Got some short ribs cooking.

1192
00:50:51,783 --> 00:50:55,351
不了, 我通常在演出完结后才用餐的
Nah. I won't eat nothing till after we finish playing.

1193
00:50:56,086 --> 00:50:58,120
你应该来看看我演出, 爸
You ought to come down, listen to me play, pop.

1194
00:50:58,122 --> 00:51:00,356
噢, 我不喜欢那些像中国音乐一样的嘈音
Oh, I don't like all that Chinese music, all that noise.

1195
00:51:00,358 --> 00:51:03,826
去洗手吧, Gabe, 我现在弄三明治
Go in there and wash up, Gabe. I'll fix you a sandwich.

1196
00:51:03,828 --> 00:51:06,529
Troy在生我的气
Troy mad at me.

1197
00:51:06,531 --> 00:51:08,130
你为何生他的气?
What you mad at Uncle Gabe for?

1198
00:51:08,132 --> 00:51:09,265
他以为Troy为了
He think Troy mad at him

1199
00:51:09,267 --> 00:51:11,133
他搬到Pearl那里而生气
'cause he moved over there to Miss Pearl's.

1200
00:51:11,135 --> 00:51:13,235
我才没有生气, 他可以住他想住的地方
I ain't mad at the man. He can live where he want to live at.

1201
00:51:13,237 --> 00:51:15,404
他为何搬到那里? Pearl小姐任何人都不喜欢
Well, what he move over there for? Miss Pearl don't like nobody.

1202
00:51:15,406 --> 00:51:17,273
噢, 她不介意他在, 还对他颇好
Oh, she don't mind him none. She treat him real nice.

1203
00:51:17,345 --> 00:51:18,445
她就不允许他唱歌而已
She just don't allow all that singing.

1204
00:51:18,475 --> 00:51:21,377
她不介意他在为她付租金, 仅此而已
She don't mind that rent he be paying. That's what she don't mind.

1205
00:51:21,379 --> 00:51:23,145
Troy, 我不想再跟你讨论此事
Troy, I ain't goin' through that with you no more.

1206
00:51:23,147 --> 00:51:24,847
他搬到那因为他想要有自己的地方
He moved over there 'cause he wanted his own place.

1207
00:51:24,919 --> 00:51:26,019
他可以随他所想的做
He can come and go as he please.

1208
00:51:26,049 --> 00:51:28,284
他可以在这里做他想做的, 我也不介意
He can come and go as he please here. I wasn't stoppin' him.

1209
00:51:28,286 --> 00:51:29,485
我也没规定他什么
I wasn't putting no rules on the man.

1210
00:51:29,487 --> 00:51:31,324
你明知道那是两码子的事
That ain't the same thing, and you know it.

1211
00:51:31,754 --> 00:51:33,292
我不想再讨论这话题
Now that's the last I wanna hear about that.

1212
00:51:33,322 --> 00:51:35,157
我不想再听到Gabe和Miss Pearl之间的事
I don't wanna hear nothin' else about Gabe and Miss Pearl.

1213
00:51:35,159 --> 00:51:36,195
还有下周...
And next week...

1214
00:51:36,197 --> 00:51:38,025
我准备好了, Rose
I'm ready for my sandwich, Rose.

1215
00:51:38,027 --> 00:51:40,129
还有下周, 当从学校来的负责人到来
And next week, when that recruiter come from that school,

1216
00:51:40,131 --> 00:51:42,598
我要你签署让Cory进美式足球队
I want you to sign that paper and go on and let Cory play football.

1217
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:44,500
我不想再听你说起此事
That'll be the last I have to hear about that.

1218
00:51:49,239 --> 00:51:51,307
Cory被录取了? 他要到哪所学校?
Cory got recruited? What school he goin' to?

1219
00:51:51,309 --> 00:51:52,875
我不想再理会Cory的事
I ain't thinking about Cory nothing.

1220
00:51:52,877 --> 00:51:55,277
那小子把这里当成他的地方
Boy walking around here smelling his piss,

1221
00:51:55,279 --> 00:51:56,612
以为可以为所欲为
thinking he gonna do what he want to do,

1222
00:51:56,614 --> 00:51:59,181
不听我的说话
irregardless of what I say.

1223
00:51:59,183 --> 00:52:01,417
Bono, 听着, 我离开理事长的办公室后
Look here, Bono, I left the commissioner's office

1224
00:52:01,419 --> 00:52:02,885
去了A&P那里
and went down to the A&P.

1225
00:52:02,887 --> 00:52:05,321
那小子根本没在那工作, 他跟我说谎了
That boy ain't workin' down there, he lied to me.

1226
00:52:05,323 --> 00:52:08,591
说他取回了工作, 周末得上班什么的
Tellin' me he got his job back, tellin' me he workin' weekend,

1227
00:52:08,593 --> 00:52:10,326
说他课后在上班
tellin' me he workin' after school.

1228
00:52:10,328 --> 00:52:12,528
Stawicki说他根本没来上班
Mr. Stawicki says he ain't working down there at all.

1229
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:13,700
Cory只是长大了而已
Cory just growing up.

1230
00:52:13,730 --> 00:52:16,198
他有了自己的想法, 不能再听你说的
He just bustin' at the seams, tryin' to fill out your shoes.

1231
00:52:16,270 --> 00:52:17,370
我才不在意他想什么
I don't care what he doing.

1232
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:19,468
当他到了反叛期
When he get to the place where he want to disobey me,

1233
00:52:19,470 --> 00:52:22,605
那就是出外打拼的时候了, Bono也懂
then it's time for him to move on. Bono will tell you that.

1234
00:52:22,607 --> 00:52:24,440
我肯定他不能违抗他父亲后
I bet he ain't never disobeyed his daddy

1235
00:52:24,442 --> 00:52:26,475
不用受罚
without paying the consequences.

1236
00:52:26,477 --> 00:52:28,644
我根本没机会违抗他
I ain't never had the chance.

1237
00:52:28,646 --> 00:52:32,481
我父亲到处走, 我根本没看过他
My daddy came on through, but I ain't never knew him to see him.

1238
00:52:32,483 --> 00:52:35,284
或者他在想什么, 去哪了
Or what he had on his mind, or where he went.

1239
00:52:35,286 --> 00:52:39,155
就四海为家, 寻找新大陆
Just moving on through. Searching out the new land.

1240
00:52:39,623 --> 00:52:42,258
那就是以前的人用的
That's what the old folks used to call it.

1241
00:52:42,260 --> 00:52:45,594
一个人要是到处搬, 不停换女人
See a fella moving around from place to place, woman to woman,

1242
00:52:45,596 --> 00:52:48,264
他们叫这"寻找新大陆"
they call it "searching out the new land."

1243
00:52:48,266 --> 00:52:49,732
我也不清楚他有没有找到
I can't say if he ever found it.

1244
00:52:50,500 --> 00:52:53,269
我来到这地方, 也不想有孩子
I come along, didn't want no kids.

1245
00:52:53,503 --> 00:52:55,538
我也不知道我能否安定下来
I didn't know if I was gonna be in one place long enough

1246
00:52:55,540 --> 00:52:57,606
当个爸爸
to fix on 'em right as their daddy.

1247
00:52:57,608 --> 00:52:59,909
我想不如还是寻找新大陆算了
I figured I was going searching, too.

1248
00:52:59,911 --> 00:53:02,278
没想过我跟Lucille在一起的时间
As it turn out, I been hooked up with Lucille

1249
00:53:02,280 --> 00:53:04,613
也几乎有你爸爸和Rose在一起那么久了
for near about as long as your daddy been with Rose.

1250
00:53:04,615 --> 00:53:06,916
已经16年了
Going on 16 years.

1251
00:53:06,918 --> 00:53:08,684
有时候我真希望自己不认识我的父亲
Sometimes, I wish I'd never known my daddy.

1252
00:53:08,686 --> 00:53:12,655
他不在意孩子过得怎样, 对他来说毫不重要
He ain't cared nothing about no kids. A kid to him wasn't nothing.

1253
00:53:12,956 --> 00:53:16,358
他只想你快点成人
All he wanted you to do was learn how to walk,

1254
00:53:16,430 --> 00:53:17,530
好让你能去工作赚钱给他
so he could start you to working.

1255
00:53:17,560 --> 00:53:21,730
吃饭时, 他总先吃, 你只吃他剩下的
Come to eating, he ate first. Anything left over, that's what you got.

1256
00:53:21,732 --> 00:53:25,201
他会吃掉所有东西, 而你只分到那么一点
Man would sit down, eat two chickens, and give you the wing.

1257
00:53:25,203 --> 00:53:28,404
爸, 别胡说了, 天下父母都会让子女吃饱
You ought to stop that, pop. Everybody feed their kids.

1258
00:53:28,406 --> 00:53:31,540
不管时势有多艰难, 天下父母都疼爱子女
No matter how hard times is, everybody care about their kids.

1259
00:53:31,542 --> 00:53:32,741
确保他们三餐温饱
Make sure they have something to eat.

1260
00:53:32,743 --> 00:53:34,643
我父亲唯一在意的
Only thing my daddy cared about

1261
00:53:34,645 --> 00:53:36,512
就是叫我们搬那一卷卷的棉花给Lubin先生
was getting them bales of cotton in to Mr. Lubin.

1262
00:53:36,514 --> 00:53:38,614
那是他唯一在意的事
That's the only thing that mattered to him.

1263
00:53:38,616 --> 00:53:40,950
以前我都在想他为何还活着
Sometimes, I used to wonder why he was still living,

1264
00:53:40,952 --> 00:53:43,652
为何魔鬼还没带走他
why the devil hadn't come and got him.

1265
00:53:43,654 --> 00:53:45,654
快把棉花搬到Lubin先生那
"Get them bales of cotton in to Mr. Lubin."

1266
00:53:45,656 --> 00:53:47,289
后来才知道我父亲欠Lubin钱
Find out he owe him money.

1267
00:53:47,291 --> 00:53:48,424
当他知道此地不宜久留时
He should have just went on and left

1268
00:53:48,426 --> 00:53:49,458
他就该跑路
when he saw he couldn't get nowhere.

1269
00:53:49,530 --> 00:53:50,630
至少我会那样做
That's what I would've done.

1270
00:53:50,660 --> 00:53:53,562
他怎留下11个孩子就走? 还有走去哪?
How he gonna leave with 11 kids? And where he gonna go?

1271
00:53:53,564 --> 00:53:56,699
他只懂耕作, 他根本无路可逃
He ain't knew nothing but how to farm. No, he was trapped.

1272
00:53:57,300 --> 00:54:00,436
我想他也知道, 但我也会为他说一句...
I think he knew it, too. But I'll say this for him...

1273
00:54:00,438 --> 00:54:02,338
他觉得他有责任照顾我们
He felt a responsibility toward us.

1274
00:54:02,340 --> 00:54:04,406
虽然不像我预期一样体贴
May not have treated us like I felt he should have,

1275
00:54:04,408 --> 00:54:06,375
但他要是没有良心
but without that responsibility,

1276
00:54:06,377 --> 00:54:08,410
大可以留下我们, 自己跑路
he could have run off and left us,

1277
00:54:08,412 --> 00:54:09,678
再另起炉灶
made his own way.

1278
00:54:09,680 --> 00:54:11,313
很多人也这样
A lot of them did.

1279
00:54:11,315 --> 00:54:12,748
你说你父亲的那一代吗?
Back in those days, what you talkin' about?

1280
00:54:12,750 --> 00:54:14,583
他们每天离开房子
They walk out their front door

1281
00:54:14,585 --> 00:54:17,786
无论多日晒雨淋, 都在街上一直走
and take off down one road or
another and just keep on walkin'.

1282
00:54:17,788 --> 00:54:19,788
对, 这才像话
There you go. That's what I'm talkin' about.

1283
00:54:19,790 --> 00:54:23,425
一直走到他们遇到下一间房子
Just keep on walking till they come to something else.

1284
00:54:23,427 --> 00:54:26,695
你没听过大迁徙吗? [一战时黑人从美国南部迁北]
Ain't you never heard of nobody having the walking blues?

1285
00:54:26,697 --> 00:54:29,465
那就是你叫那些跑路的人
Now, that's what you call it when you just take off like that.

1286
00:54:29,467 --> 00:54:33,369
我父亲不是你说的那种
My daddy ain't had no walking blues. What you talking about?

1287
00:54:33,371 --> 00:54:34,737
他留下来了
He stayed right there with his family,

1288
00:54:35,605 --> 00:54:39,608
但他坏事做尽
but he was just as evil as he could be!

1289
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:43,445
我妈妈接受不了他和他的性格
My mama couldn't stand him. Couldn't stand that evilness.

1290
00:54:43,447 --> 00:54:46,482
我8岁时她就离开了
She run off when I was about eight.

1291
00:54:46,484 --> 00:54:49,618
她有一晚静悄悄的走, 跟我说她会回来
She sneaked off one night, told me she was coming back for me.

1292
00:54:49,620 --> 00:54:51,487
自那我就再没有见过她
I ain't never seen her no more.

1293
00:54:51,489 --> 00:54:55,658
他有过的女人终究都会离开他, 他不是个好人
All his women run off and left him. He wasn't good for nobody.

1294
00:54:56,293 --> 00:54:57,760
轮到我离家的时候
My turn come to head out.

1295
00:54:57,762 --> 00:54:59,361
我当时14岁
I was 14,

1296
00:54:59,363 --> 00:55:02,364
跟Joe Canewell的女儿打得火热
got to sniffing around Joe Canewell's daughter.

1297
00:55:03,567 --> 00:55:05,801
我们家有只老骡子叫Greyboy
We had this old mule called "Greyboy".

1298
00:55:05,803 --> 00:55:08,337
我父亲叫我出去耕作
My daddy sent me out to do some plowing.

1299
00:55:08,339 --> 00:55:11,807
让我有机会跟Joe Canewell的女儿谈谈情
I got to fooling around with Joe Canewell's daughter.

1300
00:55:11,809 --> 00:55:15,377
我们找到了一个隐蔽的地方抚摸大家
Found us a nice spot, got real cozy with each other.

1301
00:55:15,379 --> 00:55:18,547
她当时13岁, 所以我们都知道大家发育了
She was about 13, so we done figured we grown anyway.

1302
00:55:18,549 --> 00:55:20,816
我们在溪河附近, 互相抚摸
So, we were down there by the creek, enjoying ourselves,

1303
00:55:20,818 --> 00:55:22,518
把正事都放一边
ain't thinking about nothing.

1304
00:55:22,520 --> 00:55:24,787
怎料绑着Greyboy的绳子松开了
Didn't know Greyboy had gotten loose,

1305
00:55:24,789 --> 00:55:28,457
它跑回家里, 我父亲就知道事有蹊跷
wandered back to the house, and my daddy was lookin' for me.

1306
00:55:28,591 --> 00:55:32,328
他找到我们时, 看到我们还在抚摸大家
So, we down there enjoying ourselves when he come up on us.

1307
00:55:32,330 --> 00:55:34,430
我们不知所措
Surprised us.

1308
00:55:34,432 --> 00:55:36,832
他拿着骡子身上的皮带
Had them leather straps off that mule,

1309
00:55:36,834 --> 00:55:40,069
开始不停地打我
commenced to whupping me like there was no tomorrow.

1310
00:55:40,071 --> 00:55:42,738
我站起来, 当时心感侮辱又愤怒
I jump up. I'm mad, embarrassed.

1311
00:55:43,406 --> 00:55:45,674
又很害怕他
I was scared of my daddy.

1312
00:55:45,676 --> 00:55:47,710
他开始打我时
Now, when he commenced to whipping on me,

1313
00:55:47,712 --> 00:55:49,578
很自然地我就逃跑吧
quite naturally, I run to get out of the way.

